<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-194-227 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 507 170</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  March 26 1991 v5 n12 p4(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Macweek 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Portfolio print utility offers mini and two-sided pages.andO;(Portfolio Systems Inc.'s DynoPage) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McManus, Neil.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Portfolio Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   DynoPage (Printer software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Printer SoftwareProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Neil McManusandM;Rhinebeck, N.Y.andP;  -- Portfolio Systems Inc. this month began shippingDynoPage, a $125 utility that brings double-sided printing, page previews anddozens of new page-size and layout options to any Mac application.andM;The program lets users output full-size or reduced versions of address lists,calendars, handbooks or almost any other document on index cards,personal-organizer pages or other smaller-than-standard pages.andM;DynoPage works by placing multiple &quot;virtual pages&quot; on each sheet fed throughthe printer.andP;  With the software installed, standard Page Setup and Printdialogs are followed by new windows offering additional options.andP;  Iconsdisplayed in a scrolling list represent available choices, includingtri-fold, half-page, and four- or six-up layouts.andP;  The program, an outgrowthof Portfolio's Dynodex address-book program, also supports the specialperforated sheets the company distributes for use in personal organizers.andM;The software lets users generate thumbnail reductions of multipage documentson a single page or preview output, even in applications that don't have apreview option.andM;Portfolio is at 21 E. Market St., Rhinebeck, N.Y.andP;  12572.andP;  Phone (914)876-7744; fax (914) 876-7747.andO;</TEXT></DOC>